In [10]:
accidents_severity = ca['Severity'].value_counts().sort_index()
if not accidents_severity.empty:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6), subplot_kw=dict(aspect="equal"))
    labels = [f'Severity {int(level)}' for level in accidents_severity.index]
    colors = sns.color_palette('Set2', len(labels))
    wedges, texts, autotexts = ax.pie(accidents_severity, labels=labels, colors=colors,autopct='%1.1f%%', pctdistance=0.85)
    circle = plt.Circle((0, 0), 0.5, color='white')
    ax.add_artist(circle)
    ax.set_title("Accidents by Severity", fontdict={'fontsize': 16})
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
else:
    print("No data available to plot accidents by severity.")

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

ca['Start_Time'] = pd.to_datetime(ca['Start_Time'], errors='coerce')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))
sns.histplot(ca['Start_Time'].dt.hour, bins=24, color='coral')
plt.xlabel("Hour of the Day")
plt.ylabel("Number of Accidents")
plt.title('Accidents Count By Time of Day')
plt.show()
